com.raweng.built

Class BuiltClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltClass

  • public class BuiltClass
extends java.lang.Object
    BuiltClass provides BuiltObject and BuiltQuery instance.
    It also provides some functionality with the Built.io Backend server.
    Author:
    built.io. Inc

        public void setHeader(java.lang.String key,
                      java.lang.String value)
        To set headers for Built.io Backend rest calls.
        Scope is limited to this object and followed classes.
        Parameters:
        key - header name.
        value - header value against given header name.

        Example :
          // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
  BuiltClass projectClass = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b").classWithUid("project");

  projectClass.setHeader("custom_key", "custom_value");

      • on

        public void on(Built.EventType eventType,
               com.raweng.built.BuiltOnEventCallback callback)
        This function registers an event listener.

        [Only avaliable with realtime]
        Parameters:
        eventType - event name.
        callback - BuiltOnEventCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Given below is the list of supported events.

        Update :- Update event is triggered when the schema and/or the ACL of this class is modified. Registered callback is invoked with the updated class data.

        Delete :- Delete event is triggered when this class is deleted. Registered callback is invoked with the deleted class data.

        Broadcast :- Broadcast event is triggered when a message is broadcast over the class instance. Registered callback is invoked with the broadcast message.



        Example :
         // 'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 BuiltApplication builtApplication  = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
 BuiltClass projectClass = builtApplication.classWithUid("project");

 projectClass.on(Built.EventType.UPDATE, new BuiltOnEventCallback() {

      @Override
      public void onReceive(Object object, BuiltError error) {

      }
 });
